# Muggle AI Documentation Repository

This is the **customer-facing documentation** for Muggle AI products. All content is publicly visible.

## Critical Guidelines

### No Sensitive Information

This documentation is **customer-facing**. NEVER include:
- Internal statistics or metrics
- Internal data (user counts, usage data, performance benchmarks)
- Internal architecture details (service names, infrastructure, database schemas)
- Internal URLs, API keys, or credentials
- Any proprietary implementation details

### No ASCII Tables or Diagrams

Do NOT use ASCII-based formatting - it is error-prone and renders inconsistently:

```markdown
<!-- ❌ BAD: ASCII tables/diagrams - spacing breaks easily -->
+--------+--------+
| Header | Header |
+--------+--------+

<!-- ✅ GOOD: Use standard Markdown tables -->
| Header | Header |
| :----- | :----- |
| Value  | Value  |

<!-- ✅ GOOD: Use Mermaid for diagrams -->
```

## Repository Structure

```
muggle-ai-docs/
├── manifest.json          # Index of all articles (MUST update when adding docs)
├── getting-started/       # Onboarding and quickstart guides
├── concepts/              # Core concepts and architecture
├── api/                   # API reference documentation
├── mcp/                   # MCP Gateway documentation
└── troubleshooting/       # Common issues and solutions
```

## Adding New Documentation

1. Create `.md` file in appropriate folder
2. **Update `manifest.json`** with new article entry:
   - Add to correct section's `articles` array
   - Include: `articleId`, `title`, `summary`, `relativePath`, `order`, `tags`
3. Follow documentation standards (see `documentation-standards.mdc`)

## Key Reminders

- This is PUBLIC documentation - no internal details, stats, or architecture
- Use Mermaid for diagrams, standard Markdown for tables
- Cross-link related articles using relative paths
